Hello all! This may be an ill-informed question, but I was just trying to mess around with some test code for working with our new MaxSwerve system, and everything worked fine with that, but now that I try importing Pathplanner, there seems to be a bunch of issues that emerge. I’ve tried going to the Pathplanner docs, but they’re pretty bare, and I couldn’t find anything similar to my issue online. Any help figuring out why the code is mad would be greatly appreciated, thanks!

Declan0811:

now that I try importing Pathplanner, there seems to be a bunch of issues that emerge.

all of those this::... lines are used to reference methods that exist within this class. The path planner library will call these methods that you tell it to perform certain tasks. For example, resetPose is a function that takes in a Pose2d object as its first and only parameter, and does something with it to reset the odometry to start at that provided pose.

You need to write that resetPose method.

private void resetPose(Pose2d startingPose) {
  // Do something with startingPose
}

Same with getRobotReleativeSpeeds and driveRobotRelative.

There errors with the DriverStation alliance seem to just be a missing imports issue

@ArchdukeTim has already answered everything.

A little suggestion: if you get errors like “xxx not defined”, “xxx not found,” or “xx cannot be resolved as…”, it means something that should have been there was not there. You can try hovering over the underlined code and see if VSCode has any suggestions. VSCode is smart enough to help you find missing import statements. When it doesn’t, you must have missed something.
